        <mj-spacer height="16px" />
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" css-class="light_img" width="150px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/gp-logo-grey.png" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" alt="" />
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 0px" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 2px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Did you know that the King of the UK receives daily updates on government affairs through a red dispatch box every morning?</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">
            <strong>In today’s weekend edition:</strong>
          </p>

          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4;  padding-left: 10px">→ Bangledesh-Pakistani Relations</p>

          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 10px">→ Greenland PM responds to Trump</p>

          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 10px">→ Palestinians return home</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 0px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-spacer height="10px"></mj-spacer>
    <!-- THIS WEEK IN GEOPOLITICS -->
    <mj-section css-class="mj_fsection" background-color="#ffffff" css-class="mj_fsection">
      <mj-spacer height="0px"></mj-spacer>
      <mj-column background-color="#ffffff" width="100%">
        <mj-text padding="2px 12px 0px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="white">
          <h2 style="
          padding-top:14px;
              color: #06266d;
              text-align: left;
              border-bottom: 2px solid #06266d;
              text-transform: uppercase;
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 300;
              padding-bottom:8px;
            ">RECAP</h2>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- Content sections -->
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.2;">
          <strong>🇧🇩 Bangladesh moves closer to Pakistan amid strains with India</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4"> 
            Pakistan-Bangladesh ties grew strong since Bangladeshi PM Sheikh Hasina's departure. Both countries now share a general <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-01-2025-r1-1-anti-india-sentiment" target="_blank">anti-India sentiment</a>. This shift has led to improved dialogue between the nations and a boost in military and diplomatic relations. Pakistan's army chief, General Asim Munir, recently met Bangladesh's Lieutenant General SM Kamrul Hassan to strengthen military ties. Pakistani military’s media wing described the countries as “brotherly nations.”
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4;filter:blur(5px);"> 
            Pakistan's PM Shehbaz Sharif met Bangladesh's interim leader, Muhammad Yunus, in Cairo last month. However, historical tensions from the <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-01-2025-r1-2-1971-war" target="_blank">1971 war</a> and unresolved issues remain between the two nations. Despite these grievances, both countries are exploring opportunities for economic cooperation, with Bangladesh's growing economy incentivizing improved ties.
          </p>
          </mj-text>
          </mj-column>
          </mj-section>
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
  </mj-body>
